                <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/2434: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Arica</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Von Tresckow</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Arica</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-06-11T14:00:00-04:42">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 11, 1926—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>From Lassiter. Your telegram June 11, 9 a.m. It might not be amiss to intimate to
                    Ambassador Cruchaga that if Chilean Commissioner will propose suspension of all
                    plebiscitary activities during period of good offices and will likewise propose
                    postponement of Commission’s action on motions to consummate as well as on
                    motions to terminate the plebiscite, the resolution which embodies such
                    proposals will receive my support. Lassiter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Von Tresckow</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
